⸻

Research Questions

Research question 1 (Fridjoff):
How does Steam account age influence the average inventory value of Counter-Strike players, and is the relationship linear or non-linear?

Research question 2 (Fridjoff):
What is the relationship between total playtime and inventory value in Counter-Strike, and does additional playtime contribute differently to inventory growth at higher experience levels?

Research question 3 (Fridjoff):
To what extent does inventory value correlate with in-game rank, and can inventory value serve as a predictor of competitive performance?

Research question 4 (Jan):
How does the frequency of gameplay sessions (activity density) correlate with inventory value compared to total lifetime hours?

Research question 5 (Jan):
To what extent does "Steam Profile Level" and community interaction (e.g., number of badges, comments, or friends) predict the rarity and value of a Counter-Strike inventory?

Research question 6 (Jan):
How does the ratio of "Consumable" items (Cases, Stickers, Graffitis) to "Skin" items (Weapons, Knives) change as an account ages?

Research question 7 (Nico):
Can a machine learning model trained on account age, playtime, Steam level, friend count, and activity density accurately predict inventory value bracket (e.g., <$50, $50–$500, >$500), and which features carry the most predictive weight?
This synthesizes all prior RQs into a capstone modeling question

Research question 8 (Nico):
How does VAC ban history or account standing correlate with inventory composition — specifically, do flagged or recently banned accounts show atypical item distributions (e.g., unusually high proportions of high-value or liquid items) compared to clean accounts?